<P><PB N="473" REF="488">COASTWISE 1766. Ships 4113.&mdash;Coals 350,803 chald.&mdash;Cinders 3716 chald.&mdash;Lead 6250 tons.</P>
<P>There are upon the river Tyne, five Gla&s;s Bottle Hou&s;es, three Broad Gla&s;s Hou&s;es, two Crown Hou&s;es, two Flint Gla&s;s Manufactories, and one Plate Gla&s;s Hou&s;e.</P>
<P>There are between 30 and 40 working Salt Pans.</P>
<P>The great Crowley Iron Manufactory at Swalwell employs three Ships, about 150 tons each, throughout the year, in carrying the produce to the port of London only, be&s;ides their great vend at other places.</P>
